[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +└── styles/               # Global styles
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +## AI Integration
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +### User-Facing AI Features
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +The monorepo allows the **extension** (`apps/extension/`) to import shared packages (`ai/`, `storage/`, `theme/`, `utils/`) without code duplication, while the web app uses a traditional feature-folder structure.
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +AI features are **optional** and require a user-provided API key:
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +                                              (Pure domain logic)
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +3. Choose model, temperature, max tokens
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +2. Enter your OpenAI API key (or custom provider config)
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +4. Click **Test Connection** to verify
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +1. Go to **Settings → AI Configuration**
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- Any OpenAI-compatible API (custom base URL)
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +**Supported providers:**
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +**AI-powered features:**
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- **Text Explanations** — AI-powered definitions and explanations for selected text
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- **Proactive Messages** — AI-driven study reminders and suggestions (optional)
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- **Vocabulary Enrichment** — AI-generated examples, synonyms, and usage notes
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- OpenAI (default)
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +### AI Architecture (for Developers)
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +```
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +Component → Feature Service → AI Package → Adapter → OpenAI-compatible API
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +```
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +The AI system uses the **Adapter Pattern** for provider-agnostic access:
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- **AI Tutor Chat** — Conversational assistant with study context
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.727Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- **Exercise Generation** — AI-generated grammar and vocabulary exercises
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- **Prompt separation** — Prompts are versioned and modular in `packages/ai/src/prompts/`
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- **Provider-agnostic** — Implement `IAiAdapter` interface to add providers
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- **Privacy-safe** — Only send data to AI on explicit user action
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- **Response validation** — All AI responses validated with Zod schemas
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- **No hard-coded API keys** — User-provided, stored in `localStorage`
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +See [docs/ai-architecture.md](docs/ai-architecture.md) for complete documentation.
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +## AI Coding Agent Integration
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +Key design principles:
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +### Codebase Conventions for AI Agents
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| **Clean Architecture** | Presentation / Application / Domain / Infrastructure layers are strictly separated |
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +This codebase is designed to be AI coding agent-friendly. The following conventions help AI assistants understand and modify the code reliably.
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- **No direct AI calls from UI** — Components go through service layer
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| **Strict TypeScript** | `strict: true` in `tsconfig.json` — leverage types for safe refactoring |
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| **Monorepo** | `apps/` for runnable applications, `packages/` for shared libraries |
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +---
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| **Repository Pattern** | Data access goes through repository interfaces in `packages/storage/` |
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| **Pure Domain Logic** | Packages like `learning-engine` have zero framework dependencies |
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| Convention | Description |
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| **Zod Validation** | All data at system boundaries is validated with Zod schemas |
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| **Feature Modules** | Each feature in `src/features/` owns its components, hooks, and services |
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +2. **Follow the data flow** — UI → Hook → Service → Repository. Never call IndexedDB directly from components
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +|-----------|-------------|
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +3. **Use existing patterns** — New features should mirror existing feature modules in `src/features/`
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| **Design Tokens** | All colors, spacing, typography use CSS custom properties from `packages/theme/` |
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +5. **Validate with Zod** — Any new data boundary should have a Zod schema
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +1. **Explore the architecture** — Start with this README and `docs/architecture.md` to understand the layer separation
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +6. **Test the domain logic** — Pure business logic belongs in `packages/` with unit tests
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +4. **Add to the right package** — Shared logic goes in `packages/`, app-specific logic stays in `apps/web/src/`
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +### Available AI Agent Tools
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +The repository includes a **CodeGraph** index (`.codegraph/`) that provides:
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- Symbol search and navigation
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +7. **Respect the codegraph** — Use `codegraph explore` before editing to understand blast radius
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- Dependency graph traversal
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +### How AI Agents Should Approach This Codebase
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- Caller/callee analysis
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- Blast radius calculation for changes
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +---
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-02T04:00:27.728Z] [INFO] [stderr] +Run `codegraph explore "<question>"` for AI-assisted code exploration.
